rove their economic health. While examining this large-scale, multi-site case, Fetterman highlights the potential for empowerment evaluation to build local capacity and sustain improvements within communities. He provides deep insights into key steps in empowerment evaluation by exploring the way that each of these phases took place in the digital villages. Additionally, the text provides evaluators with real-world stories and practical advice from the front lines. The Digital Village case also demonstrates the social value of combining corporate philanthropy, academic prowess, and community empowerment-highlighting the role of evaluation in this process.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 0aCommunity developmentxCase studiesxEvaluationxUnited States. 0aCommunity developmentzUnited StatesxEvaluationvCase studies. 0aDigital dividexCase studiesxUnited States. 0aDigital dividezUnited StatesvCase studies. 0aEvaluation research (Social action programs)xCase studiesxUnited StatesxUnited States. 0aEvaluation research (Social action programs)zUnited StatesvCase studies. 0aSocial justicexCase studiesxUnited States. 0aSocial justicezUnited StatesvCase studies. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Decision-Making & Problem Solving.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311070420440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978080478425240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804784252423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780804784252.jpg  a978-3-11-070420-4  SUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles